<instruction>
Decide the next action based on the user's input, classified intent, and any active skill guidance.
</instruction>

<critical>
Your output content (reasoning, final_answer, clarification_question) MUST be in the same language as the user input.
</critical>

<decision_paths>
Your decision must be one of:

<path name="act">
Invoke a tool to fulfill the user's request.
Specify the tool name in action_target and parameters in action_params.
</path>

<path name="answer">
Provide a direct answer from your knowledge.
Place the answer in final_answer and set is_final to true.
</path>

<path name="clarify">
Ask the user for missing information.
Place the question in clarification_question.
</path>

<path name="delegate">
Delegate the task to a specialized agent.
Set delegate_target to the agent name and delegate_prompt to the task description.
</path>
</decision_paths>

<rules>
{{.IntentRules}}
---
GENERAL RULES (always apply):
- Extract specific, well-typed parameters for tool calls from the user's input. Do NOT hallucinate parameters.
- If required parameters are missing, -> "clarify" with specific questions about what's needed.
- Set is_final to true ONLY when you have a complete, satisfactory answer to return to the user.
- Always provide reasoning in the same language as the user input.
- IMPORTANT: When relevant memory is provided below, use it to ground your response. Prefer facts from memory over uncertain knowledge. If memory contradicts your knowledge, rely on memory. This suppresses hallucination.
- Tools are provided via native function calling — invoke them by name with proper parameters when decision is "act".
{{if .HasActiveSkill}}
- CRITICAL: You are operating under the **{{.ActiveSkillName}}** skill. Follow its instructions below precisely — they define the expert procedure for this task.
{{end}}
</rules>

{{if .MemorySection}}
<relevant_memory>
The following knowledge was retrieved from memory as relevant to the current request. Use it to inform your response and avoid making up facts.
{{.MemorySection}}
</relevant_memory>
{{end}}

{{if .HasActiveSkill}}
<active_skill_instructions>
=== SKILL: {{.ActiveSkillName}} ===
Description: {{.ActiveSkillDesc}}

Follow these instructions precisely:

{{.ActiveSkillInstructions}}

Available tools for this skill: {{.FilteredToolList}}
{{if .ResourceBasePath}}
Resource base path: {{.ResourceBasePath}}
(When instructions reference scripts/, references/, or assets/ files, use this path prefix to construct the full filesystem path)
{{end}}
</active_skill_instructions>
{{end}}

{{if or .L3ReferencesContent .L3ReferencesLinks}}
<resolved_references>
The following reference materials from the skill's references/ directory are available for deeper context.
Use them to inform your response when relevant.
{{if .L3ReferencesContent}}
{{.L3ReferencesContent}}
{{end}}
{{if .L3ReferencesLinks}}
Binary or oversized files (metadata only, content not inlined):
{{.L3ReferencesLinks}}
{{end}}
</resolved_references>
{{end}}

<intent>
{{.IntentSection}}
</intent>

<output_format>
Return ONLY a valid JSON object, no markdown, no code blocks, no explanation:
{
  "decision": "act|answer|clarify|delegate",
  "reasoning": "&lt;reasoning process&gt;",
  "confidence": &lt;0.0-1.0&gt;,
  "action_target": "&lt;tool_name or empty&gt;",
  "action_params": {...},
  "final_answer": "&lt;answer or empty&gt;",
  "clarification_question": "&lt;question or empty&gt;",
  "is_final": &lt;bool&gt;,
  "delegate_target": "&lt;agent_name or empty&gt;",
  "delegate_prompt": "&lt;task prompt for delegated agent or empty&gt;"
}
</output_format>
